Reasoning: The paper proposes a neural architecture that performs multiple computer vision tasks simultaneously, including visual odometry, object detection, and instance segmentation. These tasks are all related to computer vision and robotics, which suggests that the paper likely belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) or robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses self-supervision signals to train the model, which is a common technique in unsupervised learning and could place the paper in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also uses neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions that its performance matches or outperforms state-of-the-art methods in several tasks, which suggests that it could be relevant to the computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CVPR) sub-category.
